# Example 4: Deterministic Off-Chain Smart Contract Engine
## Production-grade implementation with verified inputs, signed runtime, dispute model, and legal evidence

This version corrects the previous design by adding:

- signed and reproducible runtime context  
- verified input chain (trust model)  
- deterministic multi-signature orchestration  
- privacy-preserving canonical storage  
- dispute and legal override flows  
- versioned execution model  
- integration with reconciliation evidence  

Core thesis (refined):

> a contract is a deterministic state machine whose execution is only as valid as the cryptographic trust chain of its inputs.

---

# 1. System boundaries (strict)

The engine **does not trust raw events**.

It only accepts:

- verified events  
- signed evidence bundles  
- deterministic runtime context  

